history.text: Hi
Hey!
Whats up
Not too much. How do you feel about the movie, The Social Network from reading about it
I have never seen the movie, but I heard that it was good. Do you have an opinion on the movie?
I always think it is fun to compare books to an actual movie. Sometimes the book is better than the movie. I wonder how the movie would compare to the book.
Who stared in the movie do you know?
Jesse Eisenberg. He has been in a few movies I have seen
and Andrew Garfield
What was the plot of the movie?
About how Mark Zuckerberg and Eduardo Saverin started facebook, and how it got started, and there was  dispute over who actually create the site
Did the movie explain why and what caused there was a dispute between the two?
It did, but I wonder what was Hollywood and what was real
Can you give a brief summary of what the movie said was the dispute?
who actually started facebook. I forget who exactly got credit for what, but I think Saverin encouraged Zuckerberg to create the site after a breakup Zuckerberg had with his then girlfriend
Was the soundtrack to the movie good?
i do not remember
Is this considered a drama?
ehh I could see how it could be. I think they were shooting for a pop culture movie
Do you know who directed the film?
david fincher
I am not a fan of long drawn out movies would this movie fit be good or bad for me?
I think it was good movie. If you are into facebook, you would find it very interesting about the whole process
What year did this movie come out in theaters
Was Justin Timberlake also in the movie?
yes! he has an interesting role
Could you please elaborate on his role?
he plays the creator of nabster
What was Nabster?
and he communicates with Zuckerberg about making facebook big
Cool I thank you for your time.
no problem I hope you get to see it sometime

uid2response.feedback: The other user provided detailed facts about the movie such as when it came out, who was in it, and a summary of the movie.  He wasn't knowledgeable when it came to knowing if the soundtrack was good.
